{
  "texts": [
    "The six primary used emotions are shown in Fig. 7.",
    "This paper used 758 images for training (Anger: 67, Fear:30, Joy: 350, Natural: 48, Sadness: 200, Surprise: 63) and 72 images for testing (Anger: 3, Fear:3, Joy: 42, Natural: 7, Sadness: 14, Surprise: 6).",
    "The autoencoder model was created as a sequential model that sequentially adds one layer and deepens the network.",
    "Each layer feeds the output to the next layer.",
    "Starting with the input layer that takes the image dimension (width and height) and the code size."
  ]
}